Firefighters have contained a fire on the lower slopes of Signal Hill and extinguished the one above Simon&#8217;s Town. CAPE TOWN - Table Mountain National Park says two fires on the mountain slopes along the South Peninsula have been contained.Firefighters have contained a fire that broke out on the lower slopes of Signal Hill earlier this afternoon.Another blaze on the slopes of the mountain above Simon's Town in Red Hill Road has been extinguished.A water bombing helicopter had to be brought in to help.Table Mountain National Park's Philip Prins said: The fire that was reported earlier this afternoon has been contained and the one that started this morning has been extinguished and the crews are currently on their way back home. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)